are proud to host, once again,

00:00:42.730 --> 00:00:45.630
this free public event
which brings together many

00:00:45.630 --> 00:00:48.810
of our country's favorite authors.

00:00:48.810 --> 00:00:51.420
We're especially grateful
to the many sponsors

00:00:51.420 --> 00:00:54.210
who make this festival possible.

00:00:54.210 --> 00:00:57.260
And we're thrilled that
the library has been able

00:00:57.260 --> 00:01:01.540
to hold this festival for 17 years.

00:01:01.540 --> 00:01:06.310
The library is thriving because of
people like you, library patrons

00:01:06.310 --> 00:01:11.730
and book lovers who not only enjoy
reading but recognize the value

00:01:11.730 --> 00:01:15.340 position:56%
that literature has for our society.

00:01:15.340 --> 00:01:19.390
Now the History and Biography Stage
has been a perennial favorite here

00:01:19.390 --> 00:01:20.850
at the book festival.

00:01:20.850 --> 00:01:23.700
Today we have a terrific lineup
of authors on this stage --

00:01:23.700 --> 00:01:25.580
a dozen in all -- and many

00:01:25.580 --> 00:01:30.780
of them are making their first
book festival appearance.

00:01:30.780 --> 00:01:33.980
Two of the authors, however --
A. Scott Berg and John Farrell --

00:01:33.980 --> 00:01:38.320 position:56%
have been with us before and we are
so pleased that they are coming back

00:01:38.320 --> 00:01:41.870
for a return appearance this year.

00:01:41.870 --> 00:01:46.160
As an additional bonus, all of
the authors here at the History

00:01:46.160 --> 00:01:49.140
and Biography Pavilion will
be signing their books right

00:01:49.140 --> 00:01:55.050
after their presentations
downstairs on the expo floor.

00:01:55.050 --> 00:01:57.840
We begin today with a panel
discussion marking the 100th

00:01:57.840 --> 00:02:01.580
anniversary of John
F. Kennedy's birth.

00:02:01.580 --> 00:02:06.500 position:56%
Three authors -- Steven Levingston,
Kathy McKeon, and Thomas Oliphant --

00:02:06.500 --> 00:02:12.030
will talk about their recent books
on this fascinating 35th president,

00:02:12.030 --> 00:02:17.100
his family, his campaign, and his
role in the civil rights effort.

00:02:17.100 --> 00:02:19.220
I'm sure this will
be an informational

00:02:19.220 --> 00:02:21.680
as well as inspiring discussion.

00:02:21.680 --> 00:02:26.720 position:56%
But before we get started, I want to
give a special thanks to Wells Fargo

00:02:26.720 --> 00:02:30.070
which has generously sponsored the
History and Biography Stage here

00:02:30.070 --> 00:02:33.010 position:56%
at the festival for seven years now.

