Wells Fargo Regional President
Michael Golden is here with us today

00:02:37.520 --> 00:02:39.720
and would like to say a few words.

00:02:39.720 --> 00:02:42.020
Mike?

00:02:49.040 --> 00:02:50.340
&gt;&gt; Michael Golden: Thank you.

00:02:50.340 --> 00:02:51.640
As Louise said, I'm Mike Golden.

00:02:51.640 --> 00:02:54.650
I serve as Regional President
for our operation here

00:02:54.650 --> 00:02:57.280
in the capital region
and it's my pleasure

00:02:57.280 --> 00:02:59.700
to have been here all seven years.

00:02:59.700 --> 00:03:02.530
My family and I relocated

00:03:02.530 --> 00:03:06.940
to the greater Washington market
almost seven years ago now,

00:03:06.940 --> 00:03:09.450
and this was the very first
event that I had the pleasure

00:03:09.450 --> 00:03:12.890
of attending publicly after we
moved here from Atlanta, Georgia.

00:03:12.890 --> 00:03:15.480
So it's been a real
pleasure to be a part

00:03:15.480 --> 00:03:17.560
of this festival for seven years.

00:03:17.560 --> 00:03:21.060
Our company, Wells
Fargo, is extremely proud

00:03:21.060 --> 00:03:25.570
to have been a charter sponsor
of the National Book Festival

00:03:25.570 --> 00:03:29.650
and also the sponsor of this
stage for all seven years.

00:03:29.650 --> 00:03:33.520
You know, we celebrate the
wonderful work that the Library

00:03:33.520 --> 00:03:37.070
of Congress does in promoting
literacy and active reading

00:03:37.070 --> 00:03:40.220
because Wells Fargo's had an
active role of promoting literacy

00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:43.960
across our country
for a quite long time.

00:03:43.960 --> 00:03:46.620
Here locally in the
greater Washington market,

00:03:46.620 --> 00:03:54.070
